==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*imbiaz'', from Indo-European ''a(m)pi-''.  Cognate with Middle Dutch [[imme]] (Dutch [[imker]] ‘beekeeper’), Old High German [[imbi]] (German [[Imme]]).  The Indo-European root is also the source of Greek [[εμπίς]], Latin [[apis]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈɪmbe/}}

===Noun===
'''imbe''' ''n''
# swarm of bees

===Notes===
Only attested in late form [[ymbe]].

